465
00:38:06,648 --> 00:38:10,311
Okay, Jarod. Jarod?

466
00:38:16,258 --> 00:38:19,284
- Jarod!
- <i>[Door Opens]</i>

467
00:38:19,361 --> 00:38:22,421
- <i>[Man] Burns in the house.!</i>
- <i>[Man #2] Word.!</i>

468
00:38:22,497 --> 00:38:25,523
[Men Shouting]

469
00:38:25,600 --> 00:38:28,535
- Bring your punk-asses out!
- <i>Let's go.!</i>

470
00:38:28,603 --> 00:38:32,130
- Don't wait for their asses.
- Jarod, where are you?

471
00:38:32,207 --> 00:38:34,437
<i>[Jarod On Headset]</i>
<i>Above you.</i>

472
00:38:34,509 --> 00:38:37,501
<i>[Phil]</i>
<i>This is not good.</i>

473
00:38:37,579 --> 00:38:39,547
<i>[On Headset]</i>
<i>It's okay. I've got you in my sights.</i>

474
00:38:39,614 --> 00:38:42,344
<i>Smile, Phil. It's showtime.</i>

475
00:38:45,687 --> 00:38:48,588
Annie, why is
the general manager here?

476
00:38:48,657 --> 00:38:50,648
I think you have
a meeting with him.

477
00:38:57,065 --> 00:38:59,397
Mr. Ferren, what a surprise.

478
00:38:59,467 --> 00:39:01,458
Nice to see you again,
Mr. Ferren.

479
00:39:01,536 --> 00:39:03,595
Show's about to begin, gentlemen.
Please take your seats.

480
00:39:03,672 --> 00:39:06,903
I'm intrigued, Rockwell. This must be
some show you've put together.

481
00:39:06,975 --> 00:39:09,910
Yes, sir. The best.

482
00:39:11,379 --> 00:39:13,870
[Men Shouting]

483
00:39:20,422 --> 00:39:23,448
- <i>[Man On TV] What?</i>
- What you want with me?

484
00:39:23,525 --> 00:39:25,459
- What's up, fool?
- <i>[Mr. Ferren] What is this, a gang fight?</i>

485
00:39:25,527 --> 00:39:28,496
- Want some of this, huh? You want some of this?
- <i>[Chris] Is that Phil?</i>

486
00:39:28,563 --> 00:39:32,090
- <i>What you got?</i>
- Jarod, these guys are gonna kill each other.

487
00:39:32,167 --> 00:39:35,694
- <i>[Jarod] It'll be great TV.</i>
- You call me here to threaten my ass?

488
00:39:36,905 --> 00:39:40,272
This is on you, dog.
Deal or die.

489
00:39:42,277 --> 00:39:45,178
[Chattering]

490
00:39:45,247 --> 00:39:48,580
<i>This is great stuff, Phil.</i>
<i>Get closer so we can pick up sound.</i>

491
00:39:48,650 --> 00:39:51,710
I've got no cover here,
you idiot!

492
00:39:52,887 --> 00:39:54,878
I'm getting out of here.

493
00:39:54,956 --> 00:39:57,356
<i>[Jarod] Don't leave now, Phil.</i>
<i>You're gonna miss the story.</i>

494
00:39:57,425 --> 00:39:59,586
<i>[Man] You want some of this?</i>
<i>Huh? You want some of this?</i>

495
00:39:59,661 --> 00:40:02,789
- <i>[Jarod] Or maybe you are the story.</i>
- [Banging]

496
00:40:02,864 --> 00:40:05,765
- What the hell is this?
- <i>[Banging]</i>

497
00:40:08,270 --> 00:40:11,433
- He's mine!
- Jarod, help me! Jarod, help me!

498
00:40:11,506 --> 00:40:14,373
- <i>Jarod.!</i>
- <i>[Men Chattering]</i>

499
00:40:15,443 --> 00:40:17,377
- Jarod, help me!
- Yeah!

500
00:40:17,445 --> 00:40:19,310
This is great.
This is great. Keep it up.

501
00:40:19,381 --> 00:40:23,818
Look what we got here, fellas.
Uh-huh.

502
00:40:26,554 --> 00:40:28,852
Dave, ready to go citywide?

503
00:40:28,923 --> 00:40:31,391
Get ready, Seattle.

504
00:40:31,459 --> 00:40:34,758
[Men Whooping]

505
00:40:34,829 --> 00:40:38,390
- So what we gonna do with this white punk?
- [Men Grumbling]

506
00:40:38,466 --> 00:40:41,162
I say we bury his sorry ass
right where he stands.

507
00:40:41,236 --> 00:40:45,070
- [Clicking]
- [Grumbling Continues]

508
00:40:45,140 --> 00:40:47,574
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Hey, it's on every channel.</i>

509
00:40:47,642 --> 00:40:49,735
<i>[Man #2]</i>
<i>Something's going on. Look at this.</i>

510
00:40:49,811 --> 00:40:53,247
<i>[Jarod] This is gonna be a great piece,</i>
<i>Phil. Just keep them talking.</i>

511
00:40:53,315 --> 00:40:55,749
<i>[Men Chattering On TV]</i>

512
00:40:55,817 --> 00:40:57,842
This guy's gonna shoot me.

513
00:40:57,919 --> 00:41:00,854
- Just like Ken Watanabe?
- What?

514
00:41:00,922 --> 00:41:03,857
<i>Jarod, come down here.!</i>

515
00:41:03,925 --> 00:41:06,655
What's up? You gonna do the deed
or not? 'Cause if you're not...

516
00:41:06,728 --> 00:41:10,357
- [Guns Cocking]
- No, no, you can't shoot me! No, you can't!

517
00:41:10,432 --> 00:41:13,026
He's got a TV camera on you.

518
00:41:13,101 --> 00:41:16,400
Cameras.
They can do wonderful things.

519
00:41:16,471 --> 00:41:20,464
But Ken Watanabe's camera
couldn't stop him from getting shot.

520
00:41:20,542 --> 00:41:23,204
I didn't know there was
gonna be shooting.

521
00:41:23,278 --> 00:41:25,473
But you did know that a rival
gang was going to be there...

522
00:41:25,547 --> 00:41:27,481
because you tipped them off...

523
00:41:27,549 --> 00:41:30,109
<i>and that's why you wore</i>
<i>a bulletproof vest.</i>

524
00:41:30,185 --> 00:41:32,119
I tipped them off.
Okay, okay!

525
00:41:32,187 --> 00:41:34,485
<i>[Jarod] You knew you were putting</i>
<i>Ken Watanabe in danger...</i>

526
00:41:34,556 --> 00:41:38,048
but you didn't care because
all you care about is getting the story.

527
00:41:38,126 --> 00:41:40,287
Yes! Please, help me!

528
00:41:40,362 --> 00:41:42,296
<i>I can't do that, Phil.</i>

529
00:41:42,364 --> 00:41:44,924
It's ratings at all costs.

530
00:41:44,999 --> 00:41:49,368
Like you always say,
"If it bleeds, it leads."

531
00:41:49,437 --> 00:41:52,998
I set him up. I set him up.
I set it up, okay?

532
00:41:55,377 --> 00:41:59,370
- You got what you need, bro?
- <i>It's a slam dunk.</i>

533
00:41:59,447 --> 00:42:02,075
I got everything
I need right here.

534
00:42:02,150 --> 00:42:05,278
[Men Laughing]

535
00:42:05,353 --> 00:42:08,186
"I set him up! I set him up!"

536
00:42:11,159 --> 00:42:15,391
[Voices, Indistinct]

537
00:42:15,463 --> 00:42:17,727
That was the money shot
you've all been waiting for.

538
00:42:17,799 --> 00:42:21,200
Jarod Crane,
<i>Channel 43 News,</i> reporting.

539
00:42:24,506 --> 00:42:26,906
[Crowd Murmuring]

540
00:42:30,812 --> 00:42:33,838
I'm holding you responsible
for this, Mr. Rockwell.

541
00:42:33,915 --> 00:42:37,351
Forget the liability this
station faces in light of this.

542
00:42:37,419 --> 00:42:39,216
You ruined a man's life.

543
00:42:39,287 --> 00:42:41,221
- Sir, l...
- Save it. Save it.

544
00:42:41,289 --> 00:42:45,487
